<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="122" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6625593" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6625593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6625593/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="122" targetBox="[191,782,968,1383]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph blockId="15.[805,1400,960,1387]" pageId="15" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[806,981,1161,1190]" pageId="15" pageNumber="122">Distribution.</emphasis>
Cordillera de Talamanca (SC Costa Rica and W Panama).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="122" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[805,1400,960,1387]" lastBlockId="15.[190,1396,1392,2331]" pageId="15" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[805,1085,1235,1268]" pageId="15" pageNumber="122">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 390-450 mm, tail 15-29 mm, ear 49-54 mm, hindfoot 90-99 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Dice’s Cottontail is large and has rudimentary tail and short ears. Dorsal pelage is a mix of blacks and browns, and sides are blackish gray. Ventral fur is whitish, except for brownish throat patch. Tail is blackish and often not visible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="122" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[190,1396,1392,2331]" pageId="15" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[193,303,1519,1544]" pageId="15" pageNumber="122">Habitat.</emphasis>
Paramos grasslands, shrublands, and oak cloud forests. Dice’s Cottontail inhabits high elevations from 1524 m in Cervantes up to 3536 m in Cerro Chirropo, Costa Rica, and 1219 m at Boquete and 1615 m at Cerro Punta, Panama.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
